rought by love; in man, by ambition\n\n- Rabindranath\n|\nNo, honestly, my mouth shouldn't be able to function unless my brain's engaged.\n\n- Jodi Picoult, Handle with Care\n|\nFaith goes hand in hand with the belief in a supreme purpose that includes everybody, a purpose that is for mankind’s ultimate peace, harmony and happiness.\n\n- Janvier Chouteu-Chando, The Union Moujik\n|\nI celebrate the connections in my life, from my past, present, and future. I joyfully accept love in all its healthy forms!\n\n- Amy Leigh Mercree, Joyful Living: 101 Ways to Transform Your Spirit and Revitalize Your Life\n|\nAll of your failures, are training grounds\n\n- Napz\n|\nEach flower is a field smile, every man is the soul of the world.\n\n- Corina\n|\nhow lacking in intuition men could be in persuading themselves that mending some stranger's socks, and attending to his comfort, could content a woman...\n\n- Daphne du Maurier, The Glass-Blowers\n|\nThat's interesting,' Bitterblue said. 'You think a conscience requires fear?\n\n- Kristin Cashore, Bitterblue\n|\nBig don't mean ugly, and thin sho don't mean pretty. If a person wants to be pretty, they gotta walk pretty, talk pretty and act pretty. Can't nobody take pretty from you.\n\n- Daniel Black, Perfect Peace\n|\nYou are the light in my darkness,Restful peace for my soul.You are the one who rescues me,Never let me go.\n\n- Lily\n|\nWell, you know, there are limits to the sacred claims of friendship.\n\n- P.G. Wodehouse, Carry on, Jeeves\n|\nI rather miss my wild girl; but if I get a strong, helpful, tender-hearted woman in her place, I shall feel quite satisfied.\n\n- Louisa\n|\nI think... if it is true that there are as many minds as there are heads, then there are as many kinds of love as there are hearts.\n\n- Leo Tolstoy, Anna Karenina\n|\nI must have flowers, always and always.\n\n- Claude\n|\nRemember, that username is a real person. Choose to spread the love online.\n\n- Amy Leigh Mercree, The Compassion Revolution: 30 